WEBVTT

00:01.875 --> 00:04.167
(narrator)
Previously on "Hellcats.."

00:04.167 --> 00:05.959
The university is pulling
our funding for regionals.

00:05.959 --> 00:07.458
So we can't move
to the next level?

00:07.458 --> 00:09.458
Oh, we qualified,
so we're free to go

00:09.458 --> 00:11.708
providing that
we can figure out
how to pay

00:11.708 --> 00:15.917
for our away uniforms,
entrance fees, travel..

00:15.917 --> 00:17.542
My stomach's been in knots
all day.

00:17.542 --> 00:18.792
Well, I thought you were
all excited about

00:18.792 --> 00:20.708
the big secular date.
What happened?

00:20.708 --> 00:22.250
Everything you said..

00:22.250 --> 00:24.208
...about what a player Dan is.

00:24.208 --> 00:26.084
Oh, this is because of me.

00:27.333 --> 00:28.625
I'm coming down.

00:28.625 --> 00:29.792
Dr. Derrick is not gonna

00:29.792 --> 00:31.625
clear you with a bum wrist.

00:31.625 --> 00:33.333
My wrist is, is fine.

00:35.167 --> 00:36.125
Ow!

00:36.125 --> 00:38.166
- I need your help.
- Mm-hmm.

00:38.166 --> 00:39.708
I have to pass medical.

00:39.708 --> 00:41.375
You told her I was a player?

00:41.375 --> 00:43.458
I'm sorry.
It was a dumb thing to say.

00:43.458 --> 00:46.042
Yeah! Now, I'm on a date
with half the squad.

00:46.042 --> 00:48.000
What do you think
you're doing?

00:48.000 --> 00:49.583
- What'd he slip you?
- Lewis, let go of my purse!

00:49.583 --> 00:50.708
Lay off of her, man.

00:50.708 --> 00:52.583
Is anybody talking to you?

00:52.583 --> 00:55.792
(Jake)
I can get you Oxy and Vikes
for the pain

00:55.792 --> 00:57.917
but you're gonna want HGH,
as well.

00:57.917 --> 00:59.417
It'll cut the healing time
in half and you can

00:59.417 --> 01:01.375
practice in the meantime.

01:01.375 --> 01:03.084
♪ One two three four ♪

01:03.084 --> 01:05.834
♪ Move to the left
move to the right ♪

01:06.959 --> 01:08.875
♪ Everybody get down
get down get down ♪

01:08.875 --> 01:10.708
♪ Everybody get down
if you feel me ♪

01:10.708 --> 01:13.000
♪ Everybody get down
get down get down ♪

01:13.959 --> 01:16.417
[all cheering]

01:16.417 --> 01:18.291
♪ Everybody get down
if you feel me ♪

01:18.291 --> 01:20.125
♪ Everybody get down
get down get down ♪

01:20.125 --> 01:23.000
♪ Everybody get down
if you feel me ♪

01:23.000 --> 01:25.084
♪ It goes one by one
even two by two ♪

01:25.084 --> 01:27.000
♪ Everybody on the floor
let me show you how we do ♪

01:27.000 --> 01:28.834
♪ Let's go dip it low then
you bring it up slow ♪

01:28.834 --> 01:30.750
♪ Wind it up one time
wind it back once more ♪

01:30.750 --> 01:32.834
♪ Come run run run run
everybody move run ♪

01:32.834 --> 01:34.667
♪ Let me see you movin'
rock till the groove done ♪

01:34.667 --> 01:36.500
♪ Shake it till the moon
becomes the sun ♪

01:36.500 --> 01:38.084
♪ Everybody in the club
give me a run ♪

01:38.084 --> 01:40.084
♪ If you ready to move
say yeah yeah ♪

01:40.084 --> 01:42.084
♪ One time for your mind
say it yeah yeah ♪

01:42.084 --> 01:43.917
♪ Well I'm ready for you
come let me show you ♪

01:43.917 --> 01:46.291
♪ You want to groove I'm gonna
show you how to move ♪

01:46.291 --> 01:48.209
Campus security.

01:48.209 --> 01:50.208
- 'What are you doing?'
- Good morning, sir.

01:50.208 --> 01:51.875
Happy Sunday.

01:53.125 --> 01:54.792
I'm sorry, is there a policy?

01:54.792 --> 01:57.084
Cheerleaders come
from other schools

01:57.084 --> 01:58.542
steal routines.

01:58.542 --> 02:00.917
I wish I could do
what those girls do.

02:00.917 --> 02:03.084
They're so beautiful
and blessed.

02:03.084 --> 02:06.667
- Don't you think?
- Yeah, they're nice.

02:06.667 --> 02:08.625
I was hoping to
get some footage
of the Cyclones

02:08.625 --> 02:10.667
to show
at my pot luck
next Sunday.

02:10.667 --> 02:13.458
All the girls
in my church
are huge fans.

02:13.458 --> 02:15.041
You see Donny,
one there at the end?

02:15.959 --> 02:17.167
He's so cute.

02:17.167 --> 02:19.917
I would totally abstain
from having sex with him.

02:21.417 --> 02:23.625
If you could make
a teeny-tiny exception

02:23.625 --> 02:25.583
it would really mean
a lot to my church group.

02:26.250 --> 02:29.042
[instrumental music]

02:30.084 --> 02:31.417
Go on. Get out of here.

02:31.417 --> 02:33.417
Thank you, sir.

02:33.417 --> 02:35.209
God bless.

02:39.000 --> 02:41.209
Man, their elevators
are flawless.

02:41.209 --> 02:42.166
Look at my sister go.

02:42.166 --> 02:44.000
I guess
her head's feeling better.

02:44.000 --> 02:46.500
(Savannah)
'They're really fantastic.
I can't go half that high.'

02:46.500 --> 02:49.209
It's not you.
Those guys are monsters.

02:49.209 --> 02:50.708
I wish our bases had that.

02:52.959 --> 02:55.542
We have a bid video to make,
and it has to be perfect

02:55.542 --> 02:57.000
if we wanna get to nationals.

02:58.500 --> 03:00.167
You don't achieve perfection

03:00.167 --> 03:02.375
by worrying about
what the competition is doing.

03:02.375 --> 03:04.708
You get there
with sweat. Move!

03:04.708 --> 03:06.250
.. [BC Jean singing
"Sandbox War"]

03:06.250 --> 03:07.333
- Come on, guys.
- Let's go.

03:07.333 --> 03:09.209
Whoo!

03:12.375 --> 03:14.208
♪ Back off ♪

03:14.208 --> 03:15.875
♪ Back down ♪

03:15.875 --> 03:19.959
♪ You're not the only one
on this playground ♪

03:19.959 --> 03:21.417
♪ You back off ♪

03:21.417 --> 03:23.333
♪ And back down ♪

03:23.333 --> 03:27.084
♪ I'm only cryin' just
to watch you drown ♪

03:27.084 --> 03:30.500
♪ In the end
you're either friend or foe ♪

03:30.500 --> 03:32.542
♪ So draw a line
if that's the way ♪

03:32.542 --> 03:34.166
♪ You want to go ♪

03:34.166 --> 03:38.208
♪ 'Cause I'll fight
till I can fight
no more no more ♪

03:38.208 --> 03:42.333
♪ And you say I'm off quote ♪

03:45.917 --> 03:48.458
Hey, we're all going to brunch
at the pub. You in?

03:48.458 --> 03:51.792
I'm actually having brunch
with Dan. It's a date.

03:52.417 --> 03:54.125
They grow up so fast.

03:54.125 --> 03:55.291
Yeah, it's all those hormones

03:55.291 --> 03:56.417
they put in the fast food.

03:56.417 --> 03:58.708
Do   not
eat that stuff.

03:58.708 --> 04:00.125
- Important safety tip.
- 'Right.'

04:00.125 --> 04:02.500
Hey, uh, good moves out there
just now, really.

04:02.500 --> 04:05.125
Oh, well, I think
I'm actually improving.

04:05.125 --> 04:09.125
Shoot, from where
I'm standing, it couldn't
get much better.

04:09.125 --> 04:11.291
Oh. Well...thanks.

04:12.250 --> 04:14.208
Hey, so, uh

04:14.208 --> 04:15.458
how about after brunch

04:15.458 --> 04:17.208
we, uh, go check out
jazz fest?

04:17.208 --> 04:20.000
I already bought tickets.

04:20.000 --> 04:21.916
Like, like a date?

04:21.916 --> 04:24.167
More actually a date.

04:24.167 --> 04:25.208
Oh. Oh.

04:25.208 --> 04:28.291
Um...what about you and Alice?

04:28.291 --> 04:30.792
[chuckles]
There is no me and Alice.

04:30.792 --> 04:32.167
Which is why you got
in a fist fight

04:32.167 --> 04:33.625
the other night defending
her honor? Yeah.

04:33.625 --> 04:36.583
Yeah, okay,
so I care about her,
I protect her

04:36.583 --> 04:39.333
but we are so done
being a couple.

04:39.333 --> 04:41.500
Really.

04:41.500 --> 04:43.667
You know, I, I'd love to

04:43.667 --> 04:46.458
but, um,...I-I'm kinda
slammed with school

04:46.458 --> 04:51.000
and the...bid video,
and, um, the law project, so.

04:51.000 --> 04:53.250
Right. No, hey, no worries.

04:53.250 --> 04:55.500
I'll, uh, I'll just give
the ticket to Darwin.

04:58.417 --> 04:59.792
Hey, we're-we're cool, right?

04:59.792 --> 05:01.917
Pfft! Shoot.
Hey, we're more than cool.

05:01.917 --> 05:03.417
You're my flyer. Come on now.

05:03.417 --> 05:05.208
- Right.
- Exactly.

05:05.208 --> 05:06.625
- Cool. Okay.
- Okay.

05:06.625 --> 05:08.209
Okay.

05:10.250 --> 05:11.500
Okay.

05:11.500 --> 05:14.041
[instrumental music]

05:16.875 --> 05:18.667
- So good.
- Here you go, Lewis.

05:18.667 --> 05:20.166
Everybody got what they need?

05:20.166 --> 05:21.625
- Yes.
- Yeah?

05:21.625 --> 05:24.417
Good, because I have
got some big news.

05:24.417 --> 05:25.500
Oh, God, don't
let her be pregnant.

05:25.500 --> 05:27.000
Oh, stop it.

05:27.000 --> 05:30.583
You, my friends, are looking
at the new bar manager.

05:30.583 --> 05:32.333
- Congrats.
- Alright.

05:32.333 --> 05:33.875
Wait, when did this happen?

05:33.875 --> 05:36.041
Well, it hasn't officially
happened yet

05:36.041 --> 05:39.750
but, uh, the old bar manager,
Selma, got fired for stealing

05:39.750 --> 05:43.417
which is exciting
because Victor here

05:43.417 --> 05:46.208
is gonna hire one of us
bar backs to replace her.

05:46.208 --> 05:48.041
Now, he has asked each of us

05:48.041 --> 05:49.917
to come up
with an event this week

05:49.917 --> 05:52.834
and whoever brings in the most
cash gets the promotion.

05:52.834 --> 05:54.458
Mm. So like a contest?

05:54.458 --> 05:55.750
- That's fun.
- I know!

05:55.750 --> 05:57.042
It will finally
give me a chance

05:57.042 --> 05:58.166
to get out from behind the bar

05:58.166 --> 05:59.959
and do something meaningful,
you know?

05:59.959 --> 06:02.708
I have always wanted to be
an event planner

06:02.708 --> 06:04.458
and this could be
a real stepping stone.

06:04.458 --> 06:06.083
What's your idea for an event?

06:06.083 --> 06:07.625
Open-mic night!

06:07.625 --> 06:09.417
'I have been telling Victor'

06:09.417 --> 06:11.084
that he needs
live entertainment here.

06:11.084 --> 06:14.041
Sports, sports, sports 24-7
gets dull.

06:14.041 --> 06:15.792
Well, they never do
open-mic night probably

06:15.792 --> 06:17.000
because there's no stage.

06:17.000 --> 06:18.375
'I mean, where are you gonna
put the singers?'

06:18.375 --> 06:19.667
We'll stick 'em somewhere.

06:19.667 --> 06:21.375
Hey, you should do something!

06:21.375 --> 06:22.583
'You should play some sting.'

06:22.583 --> 06:23.834
Oh. Oh.

06:23.834 --> 06:26.000
My daughter's very gifted.

06:26.000 --> 06:27.708
Well, where are you gonna
put the piano?

06:27.708 --> 06:30.042
I mean, the drum kit,
speakers? What?

06:30.042 --> 06:32.000
Do you have a sound system?
How about promotion?

06:32.000 --> 06:33.417
Details.

06:33.417 --> 06:34.917
Uh, as planner of the event

06:34.917 --> 06:36.250
aren't the details
kind of your department?

06:38.125 --> 06:40.834
Why do you have to be so mean
to me in front of our friends?

06:40.834 --> 06:43.792
- Oh, our friends?
- I'm really excited
about this.

06:46.625 --> 06:48.083
Do you want me to help you?

06:48.083 --> 06:49.166
Would you?

06:49.166 --> 06:51.083
[whispering]
Please.

06:51.083 --> 06:52.500
Okay.

06:52.500 --> 06:55.000
Look, it's not brain surgery,
okay? We can make this happen.

06:55.000 --> 06:57.041
Um, Lewis, can you throw
together some plans

06:57.041 --> 06:58.125
for a small stage
over there

06:58.125 --> 06:59.959
with room
for cabling underneath?

06:59.959 --> 07:02.125
Uh, yeah. No problem.

07:02.125 --> 07:03.291
You can do that?

07:03.291 --> 07:04.875
He's majoring in architecture.

07:04.875 --> 07:06.167
(Marti)
'Oh, and Dan can score us
some lumber from down'

07:06.167 --> 07:07.792
at the docks,
he can get us hardware

07:07.792 --> 07:08.875
and whatever tools we need.

07:08.875 --> 07:10.750
Hey, I'll just make a list.

07:10.750 --> 07:13.458
Oh, thank you, honey!
You, too, Lewis.

07:13.458 --> 07:15.708
Okay, correct me if I'm wrong,
but I thought you were trying

07:15.708 --> 07:19.000
to be   less
involved
in your mom's life.

07:19.000 --> 07:22.208
Well, two years ago,
my mom left a good
office job to come work

07:22.208 --> 07:24.625
at The Rat's, so I could get
a free ride to Lancer.

07:24.625 --> 07:26.125
And if she's got a shot
at a promotion

07:26.125 --> 07:27.625
I've got to help her.

07:27.625 --> 07:29.042
Yeah, right.

07:29.042 --> 07:31.125
- What?
- You're so transparent.

07:31.125 --> 07:34.167
A promotion means Wanda takes
on more responsibility

07:34.167 --> 07:37.333
which means longer hours,
which means less time

07:37.333 --> 07:38.834
for her to spend bugging you.

07:38.834 --> 07:40.583
- That's not why
I'm doing this.
- Liar.

07:40.583 --> 07:42.208
- I'm not!
- Still fibbing.

07:42.208 --> 07:44.333
Okay, maybe
it crossed my mind.

07:44.333 --> 07:47.084
- Half truth.
- Will you knock it off?

07:47.084 --> 07:48.167
Oh, my gosh.

07:48.750 --> 07:50.917
"Waterloo Bridge."

07:50.917 --> 07:54.166
Did your parents ever let you
see any movies after 1950?

07:54.166 --> 07:57.667
[chuckles]
I lived for pre-Hays Code DVDs

07:57.667 --> 07:59.959
and you're stalling,
Mr. Movie Know-it-all.

07:59.959 --> 08:03.000
Director or star,
"Waterloo Bridge."

08:03.000 --> 08:04.333
Carol Lombard.

08:04.333 --> 08:06.625
Mae Clarke.
That's four. I win!

08:06.625 --> 08:09.291
How do I know you're not
just making that up?

08:09.291 --> 08:11.583
- I would never lie to you.
- Uh-huh.

08:11.583 --> 08:14.084
Besides, people tell me
I'm a terrible liar.

08:14.084 --> 08:18.208
- Which isn't
such a bad thing.
- Tell me a lie.

08:21.333 --> 08:23.209
I don't like you.

08:24.750 --> 08:27.708
And as far as
you're concerned,
I'm not a fan.

08:27.708 --> 08:30.041
Ooh! The truth hurts.

08:31.834 --> 08:33.625
Savannah?

08:34.041 --> 08:35.917
Dad.

08:35.917 --> 08:37.000
W-what are you doing here?

08:37.000 --> 08:38.750
Well, we have just
come from church.

08:38.750 --> 08:41.833
You probably don't remember,
but it's right up the block.

08:42.833 --> 08:44.959
Who's your friend?

08:44.959 --> 08:48.291
Oh, um,
this is my boyfriend, Dan.

08:50.125 --> 08:52.291
This is my mom, Layne,
my dad, Parker

08:52.291 --> 08:54.250
'and I think you
remember Charlotte.'

08:54.250 --> 08:55.458
Hey, uh, Dan Patch.

08:55.458 --> 08:57.583
It's, um,
great to meet you all.

08:57.583 --> 08:59.750
Hope that head's
feeling better, Charlotte.

08:59.750 --> 09:01.542
I'm finally back
cheering with the Cyclones.

09:01.542 --> 09:05.167
Mm-hmm,
against my better judgment.

09:05.167 --> 09:06.750
I've been praying for you.

09:09.959 --> 09:11.083
It's good to see you, daddy.

09:11.083 --> 09:12.792
Good to see you, too, honey.

09:14.125 --> 09:16.875
[instrumental music]

09:16.875 --> 09:18.084
Why don't you and Dan
come around

09:18.084 --> 09:20.000
for dinner sometime this week?

09:20.000 --> 09:21.000
Really?

09:21.000 --> 09:22.125
'Parker, I'm sure that'

09:22.125 --> 09:24.041
Savannah and her boyfriend

09:24.041 --> 09:26.583
have better things to do.

09:26.583 --> 09:27.750
No, we don't.

09:27.750 --> 09:29.041
I mean...do we?

09:29.041 --> 09:33.083
Ah...nothing that beats
fine food and good company.

09:34.000 --> 09:36.083
So it's settled.

09:36.083 --> 09:38.167
- Thanks, dad.
- Mm-hmm.

09:38.750 --> 09:40.834
And, mom.

09:41.834 --> 09:43.542
I miss you all so much.

09:45.167 --> 09:47.166
I haven't sat down for dinner
with my family

09:47.166 --> 09:49.333
in more than a year..

09:49.333 --> 09:51.208
...since I left Mem-Chris.

09:51.208 --> 09:54.125
Maybe my mom is finally ready
to let me back in.

09:54.125 --> 09:55.250
This is so good.

09:55.250 --> 09:57.000
I'm really happy for you,
Savannah.

09:57.000 --> 09:59.291
- Family's important.
- Thanks.

09:59.291 --> 10:01.208
And thank you
for being so polite.

10:01.208 --> 10:03.209
Hey, it's my pleasure.

10:03.209 --> 10:05.083
You know,
I couldn't help but notice

10:05.083 --> 10:08.041
you introduced me
as your boyfriend.

10:08.041 --> 10:10.917
Oh. Is that a problem?

10:10.917 --> 10:14.084
Ah, I just didn't expect
to hear you call me that.

10:14.084 --> 10:15.792
It kinda threw me.

10:15.792 --> 10:17.125
It just sort of slipped out.

10:17.125 --> 10:19.583
No, I totally get it.

10:19.583 --> 10:22.375
I like you, Savannah.
I mean, I really do.

10:22.375 --> 10:24.083
And I wouldn't
want to hurt you

10:24.083 --> 10:27.209
but we need to make sure
we're on the same page.

10:28.167 --> 10:30.083
I mean, I'm not exclusive
with anybody.

10:32.375 --> 10:34.000
You're seeing other women?

10:34.000 --> 10:38.250
No, I haven't since we met,
but...I reserve the right to.

10:38.250 --> 10:41.000
And you should feel free
to do the same.

10:41.000 --> 10:43.875
I keep my promises,
so I'm careful

10:43.875 --> 10:45.500
to only make ones I can keep.

10:47.041 --> 10:50.125
You okay with that?

10:50.125 --> 10:52.208
Um, sure. Yeah.

10:52.208 --> 10:54.250
You'd tell me if you weren't?

10:54.875 --> 10:56.792
[chuckles]

10:56.792 --> 10:58.625
Everyday I get thrown
high into the air

10:58.625 --> 11:01.291
and slammed head first
on to a two-inch mat

11:01.291 --> 11:03.167
with a smile on my face.

11:03.167 --> 11:06.208
It's takes a lot more
than some scrawny
Irish guy to hurt me.

11:06.208 --> 11:09.583
- You sure?
- Yeah. We're having fun.

11:09.583 --> 11:11.625
You know, why mess it up
with all kinds of dumb labels?

11:11.625 --> 11:13.542
Okay. Cool.

11:14.959 --> 11:17.083
Scrawny? Really?

11:18.084 --> 11:19.792
The truth hurts.

11:43.875 --> 11:45.750
Oh.

11:45.750 --> 11:47.500
Allergies are killing me.

11:47.500 --> 11:48.875
Yeah. It's that time of year.

11:48.875 --> 11:50.417
- Mm.
- Mm-hmm.

11:53.166 --> 11:55.250
Stay out of my purse!

11:55.250 --> 11:57.084
Come on,
you big freakin' goon!

11:57.084 --> 11:58.291
[dramatic music]

11:58.291 --> 12:00.250
Allergies? Allergies, Alice?

12:00.250 --> 12:01.917
It's none of your business.

12:03.209 --> 12:04.667
What are you doing? Really?

12:04.667 --> 12:07.083
Nothing yet, okay?

12:08.959 --> 12:11.042
My wrist is healed,
but it's weak.

12:11.042 --> 12:12.875
If I hit it wrong, it hurts.

12:14.084 --> 12:16.542
I always hit it wrong
with Darwin.

12:16.542 --> 12:19.500
I don't trust him
like I trust you.

12:19.500 --> 12:22.167
I'm tentative,
and you know how dangerous

12:22.167 --> 12:23.625
that can be for a flyer.

12:25.084 --> 12:27.250
Look, I know
it was stupid,

12:27.250 --> 12:30.209
but I have to get
my spot back.

12:30.667 --> 12:33.125
You know my dad.

12:33.125 --> 12:34.917
I can't play football
like my brothers

12:34.917 --> 12:37.084
so this is all that I can do.

12:37.084 --> 12:39.291
This stuff is going
to screw you up.

12:39.291 --> 12:43.333
Please, work with me.

12:43.333 --> 12:46.667
Help me fly and I will
flush the drugs right now.

12:48.750 --> 12:51.042
(Dan)
'This is what gets you
a free ride to nationals.'

12:51.042 --> 12:54.125
Is there even a person
behind the camera? Come on.

12:54.125 --> 12:56.167
You don't have to go
to my parents' house with me.

12:56.167 --> 12:58.708
- Why don't you want me to go?
- I may not even go myself.

12:58.708 --> 13:01.166
I thought you were excited to
get back in with your parents.

13:01.166 --> 13:03.042
I am, more than anything.

13:03.042 --> 13:05.083
I'm just, I'm not sure
they want me back.

13:05.083 --> 13:06.500
I think they want
the old Savannah.

13:06.500 --> 13:08.042
Well, how is the old Savannah
different

13:08.042 --> 13:09.208
from this year's model?

13:09.208 --> 13:12.458
I go to a secular school,
I live away from home

13:12.458 --> 13:15.750
I live in a co-ed situation,
I kiss boys in public.

13:15.750 --> 13:17.625
Oh! So I'm one of the issues?

13:17.625 --> 13:19.959
And sometimes
you're the entire
subscription.

13:19.959 --> 13:21.750
How long you've been keeping
that one in your back pocket?

13:21.750 --> 13:25.458
Eons. So what'd you do wrong,
and how do we punish you?

13:25.458 --> 13:27.291
Savannah's hesitant
to parade a heathen

13:27.291 --> 13:30.166
in front of her
very proper parents at dinner.

13:30.166 --> 13:31.583
I just don't want them
to tell me

13:31.583 --> 13:33.500
how to live my life,
but I don't wanna give them

13:33.500 --> 13:35.041
anything else
to disapprove of, either.

13:35.041 --> 13:37.083
They won't understand
about you and me.

13:37.083 --> 13:38.792
The idea
of a casual relationship

13:38.792 --> 13:40.208
'would make
my mom's head explode.'

13:40.208 --> 13:41.583
So we don't tell them.

13:41.583 --> 13:43.125
It'll be fine. Parents dig me.

13:43.125 --> 13:44.959
- He does clean up well.
- That's good to know.

13:44.959 --> 13:46.375
'Here's the thing
with families.'

13:46.375 --> 13:47.667
Having a guest in the room

13:47.667 --> 13:49.792
forces the hostility
where it belongs

13:49.792 --> 13:51.750
seething just
below the surface.

13:51.750 --> 13:53.667
So we get through this,
you're gonna be back on

13:53.667 --> 13:57.084
speaking terms
with your folks.
Guaranteed.

13:58.125 --> 13:59.667
Okay. I'll call to confirm.

13:59.667 --> 14:01.667
- Great.
- Thanks. It means
a lot to me.

14:04.125 --> 14:06.834
Hey, why'd she call
your relationship casual?

14:06.834 --> 14:09.000
That girl wouldn't know casual
if it walked up to her

14:09.000 --> 14:10.375
and said, hey, yeah, whatever.

14:10.375 --> 14:11.667
We had
the non-exclusivity talk.

14:11.667 --> 14:14.167
- You didn't.
- It went pretty well.

14:14.167 --> 14:15.750
It's the same understanding
I have with Rosalie--

14:15.750 --> 14:17.708
A-and Sasha and Britt
and the assembled

14:17.708 --> 14:19.125
slut legions of Beale Street.

14:19.125 --> 14:21.125
Dude, I have to live
with these cheerleaders.

14:21.125 --> 14:24.708
I swear, Dan Patch,
if you crush
my roomie's heart..

14:24.708 --> 14:26.542
...I'm taking
the little off the bottom.

14:29.167 --> 14:31.542
♪ Whoo ♪

14:35.083 --> 14:38.625
You know, I kinda
pictured it more in
the center of that wall.

14:38.625 --> 14:40.209
Yeah, well, there's not
enough lumber, mom

14:40.209 --> 14:42.625
and you'd just have dead space
on either side of it.

14:42.625 --> 14:44.333
Are you sure this isn't
costing me anything?

14:44.333 --> 14:46.000
- Positive, Victor.
- Okay.

14:46.000 --> 14:49.041
Thrift. That's a good quality
for a manager.

14:49.041 --> 14:51.500
[instrumental music]

14:51.500 --> 14:54.166
Hey, uh, Lewis, thanks, man.
I owe you big time.

14:54.166 --> 14:55.875
Oh, it's no problem.

14:58.375 --> 15:02.291
Mm. I don't think
promoting this online
is gonna work.

15:02.291 --> 15:03.667
Well, you hijacked
all the cheerleaders

15:03.667 --> 15:05.792
as Facebook friends,
the lady doth protest--

15:05.792 --> 15:08.542
Alright, don't flaunt
your education.
It is unseemly.

15:08.542 --> 15:11.750
This bar runs on foot traffic.
We need those little posters.

15:11.750 --> 15:13.583
Oh, well, this is the viral
version of posters, okay?

15:13.583 --> 15:15.708
- Much wider audience.
- Alright. Alright. Alright.

15:15.708 --> 15:17.667
We will do it
your way as usual.

15:19.208 --> 15:21.084
Well, someone
is checking us out

15:21.084 --> 15:23.458
and by us, I mean you.

15:23.458 --> 15:25.125
- Do not encourage him.
- Why the hell not?

15:25.125 --> 15:27.084
Look, he asked me out
and I blew him off.

15:27.084 --> 15:28.625
Oh! With that body?

15:28.625 --> 15:30.667
If you're not interested,
I will take a swing at that.

15:30.667 --> 15:32.041
Not if you want
a stage, you won't.

15:32.041 --> 15:34.000
Alright, you know what, honey?

15:35.333 --> 15:36.417
You need to open up.

15:36.417 --> 15:38.375
I mean, we all have dry spells

15:38.375 --> 15:40.084
but you haven't dated
since Aaron

15:40.084 --> 15:42.500
and that was two years ago,
which makes you

15:42.500 --> 15:44.917
and I, I say this with love,
pathetic.

15:44.917 --> 15:47.834
Wow. Um, thanks, mom. Yeah,
you really bucked me up there.

15:47.834 --> 15:49.333
Look, Lewis and I
are teammates

15:49.333 --> 15:50.917
and I just, I don't
wanna complicate things.

15:50.917 --> 15:53.041
Okay, that's one
of the six lies
that we tell ourselves.

15:53.041 --> 15:56.834
They talk about it
all the time at
The Learning Annex.

15:56.834 --> 15:59.209
Alright, you haven't been
with anyone since Aaron

15:59.209 --> 16:02.208
which means that you have
inherited my trust issues.

16:02.208 --> 16:03.750
My love life is not about you!

16:03.750 --> 16:06.208
Shh, I mean, you might as well
hang a sign around your neck

16:06.208 --> 16:09.167
that says,
"I am sexually frustrated."

16:09.167 --> 16:12.209
I mean, Marti,
are you a lesbian?

16:12.209 --> 16:13.542
- Come out to momma.
- Okay, fine!

16:13.542 --> 16:14.708
You know what,
I'll just go out with him.

16:14.708 --> 16:16.041
J-just stop talking. Please!

16:16.041 --> 16:18.166
Wow. Oh, my gosh!

16:18.166 --> 16:20.708
[Fefe Dobson
singing "Stuttering"]

16:20.708 --> 16:23.375
♪ There's
a whole lot of things
that I will forgive ♪

16:23.375 --> 16:25.834
♪ But I just can't
take a liar ♪

16:25.834 --> 16:28.667
♪ I was by your side
till the very end ♪

16:28.667 --> 16:31.542
♪ Till you pushed me
in the fire ♪

16:31.542 --> 16:34.208
♪ I tried to believe you ♪

16:34.208 --> 16:37.209
♪ But something is wrong ♪

16:37.209 --> 16:40.084
♪ You won't look in my eyes ♪

16:40.084 --> 16:43.333
♪ Tell me what's going on.. ♪

16:43.333 --> 16:45.125
Oh, my God.

16:45.125 --> 16:47.125
Whoo!

16:47.125 --> 16:49.167
That felt fantastic.

16:49.167 --> 16:52.250
Are you sure it wasn't
too much on your wrist?

16:52.250 --> 16:53.959
You were never
too much for me, Lewis.

16:53.959 --> 16:55.208
Okay. Uh-uh.

16:55.208 --> 16:57.708
See, this is just
what I was talking about

16:57.708 --> 16:59.250
when I agreed to help you
get more comfortable

16:59.250 --> 17:01.708
with some of the moves
from the new bid video.

17:01.708 --> 17:05.250
No fooling around, alright?
Just practice.

17:05.250 --> 17:07.583
- Okay, boss.
- Alright. Yeah.

17:07.583 --> 17:09.458
Hey, let's try
that new pinwheel sequence

17:09.458 --> 17:11.375
from the Mem-Chris video.

17:11.375 --> 17:15.041
Hm, they do grow them
fearless at your house.

17:15.041 --> 17:16.834
Daddy disowned
all the cowards.

17:16.834 --> 17:18.250
Uh, so I see.

17:18.250 --> 17:20.583
[chuckles]
Alright.

17:20.583 --> 17:23.165
♪ You can tell me this
you can tell me that ♪

17:23.165 --> 17:26.000
♪ But don't say
you don't remember ♪

17:26.000 --> 17:28.375
♪ 'Cause I know you better.. ♪

17:28.375 --> 17:31.875
Whoa, whoa! Oh! Ho, ho!

17:31.875 --> 17:33.375
Aah...gosh.

17:33.375 --> 17:37.084
♪ I'm crazy
I know very well.. ♪

17:37.084 --> 17:38.041
Whoa! Wait. Hey.

17:38.041 --> 17:40.125
Hey, no, Alice,
we can't do this.

17:40.125 --> 17:42.166
- We cannot.
- Why not?

17:42.166 --> 17:44.583
Because I do not wanna
get back together again.

17:44.583 --> 17:46.500
It's..

17:46.500 --> 17:48.041
It's just too much drama.

17:48.041 --> 17:51.333
Look, I know, okay?
I hate it, too.

17:51.333 --> 17:53.500
But that doesn't mean
that we can't..

17:53.500 --> 17:56.208
...enjoy each other's company
now and then.

17:56.208 --> 17:58.041
♪ You're so guilty ♪

17:58.041 --> 17:59.250
♪ 'Cause you're stutterin' ♪

17:59.250 --> 18:01.959
♪ Oh oh oh.. ♪

18:01.959 --> 18:03.417
No strings.

18:03.417 --> 18:04.917
♪ Yeah you're stutterin'.. ♪

18:04.917 --> 18:07.125
Alice, what are you..

18:07.125 --> 18:09.167
Alice, wha..

18:09.167 --> 18:10.000
I promise.

18:10.000 --> 18:12.583
♪ Oh oh oh oh eh eh eh ♪

18:12.583 --> 18:15.417
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh
yeah you're stutterin' ♪

18:15.417 --> 18:18.125
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh
eh eh eh eh ♪

18:18.125 --> 18:21.583
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh
yeah you're stutterin' ♪

18:30.667 --> 18:33.084
Guess you worked up
an appetite, huh?

18:33.084 --> 18:36.250
- Hm?
- Helping down at the pub.

18:36.250 --> 18:39.625
Oh, yeah, no. Absolutely.
How's it going down there?

18:39.625 --> 18:41.291
Uh, good, yeah, uh..

18:41.291 --> 18:44.000
I'm-I'm actually heading
back in a sec for
a last-minute check.

18:47.458 --> 18:50.667
Um, listen, I've, I've been
thinking about your offer

18:50.667 --> 18:55.042
to go out sometime,
and I'd, I'd like to.

18:55.042 --> 18:57.041
You'd, uh, go out with me?

18:57.041 --> 19:00.041
I was in this
big relationship,
a couple of years back.

19:00.041 --> 19:01.875
It didn't end well.

19:01.875 --> 19:04.166
I think I ended up
with some trust issues.

19:04.166 --> 19:06.917
Anyways, if I can
depend on you
to toss me around

19:06.917 --> 19:09.542
and catch me on
the first bounce

19:09.542 --> 19:13.083
I think we should be able to
listen to some music together.

19:13.083 --> 19:16.792
Uh, Brokedown Cadillac
is playing at Hi-Tone
tomorrow.

19:16.792 --> 19:20.625
- You interested?
- Oh. Yeah. Absolutely.

19:20.625 --> 19:22.167
Great, we, can, uh,
we can go out

19:22.167 --> 19:23.041
after my mom's
thing at the pub.

19:23.041 --> 19:25.166
- Great. Okay--
- Great.

19:25.166 --> 19:26.959
Great.

19:31.625 --> 19:33.042
Great.

19:33.042 --> 19:34.041
It's quite the spread, Layne.

19:34.041 --> 19:36.792
- 'Oh. Thank you.'
- It's really good, mom.

19:36.792 --> 19:38.250
You must have spent the entire
day in the kitchen.

19:38.250 --> 19:39.625
Oh, I did.

19:39.625 --> 19:41.708
This is delicious,
Mrs. Monroe.

19:41.708 --> 19:43.458
Layne is an excellent cook.

19:43.458 --> 19:44.875
You know, my mama used to say

19:44.875 --> 19:47.042
"You cannot serve ham
without sweet potatoes."

19:47.042 --> 19:49.500
It's like laughter
without mirth.

19:49.500 --> 19:52.625
- You say that, too.
- Well, it's the truth.

19:52.625 --> 19:55.000
You know,
I think my mama said that.

19:55.000 --> 19:56.125
I swear, you Southern ladies

19:56.125 --> 19:57.792
you gotta start getting
some new lines.

19:57.792 --> 19:59.583
[all chuckling]

19:59.583 --> 20:02.000
Hm. We are all adorable.

20:04.875 --> 20:06.250
Do you spend
much time at home, Dan?

20:06.250 --> 20:07.834
I do. Yeah.

20:07.834 --> 20:11.792
My, um, my mom passed away
two years ago, November

20:11.792 --> 20:13.583
'so I moved back in
with my dad to help out.'

20:13.583 --> 20:15.209
- Really?
- 'Things have been tight.'

20:15.209 --> 20:17.583
It's kinda...made more sense
to pay rent

20:17.583 --> 20:19.250
to my family than a stranger.

20:19.250 --> 20:20.458
Hm.

20:20.458 --> 20:21.959
What church do you go to, Dan?

20:21.959 --> 20:24.083
Or do you just brunch
on Sundays?

20:24.083 --> 20:26.000
Don't pick, Charlotte.

20:27.209 --> 20:28.667
Thank you.

20:28.667 --> 20:30.125
It's just a question.

20:32.000 --> 20:35.125
Do you have a church, Dan?

20:36.209 --> 20:39.417
I am partial
to the Sunrise Gospel Mass

20:39.417 --> 20:41.209
at New Bethel on Henry Street

20:41.209 --> 20:44.000
'but I haven't really settled
on one church.'

20:44.000 --> 20:46.291
Guess I'm Paul
on the road to Damascus.

20:46.291 --> 20:49.333
Just trusting
the good Lord's gonna lead me

20:49.333 --> 20:51.000
where I need to go.

20:51.000 --> 20:53.042
Well, maybe he'll lead you
to All Saints with Savannah

20:53.042 --> 20:54.375
'one of these Sundays.'

20:54.375 --> 20:57.208
Yeah, wouldn't be surprised.

20:57.208 --> 20:59.708
That is a great idea.

21:01.000 --> 21:02.417
Could I have some
more of these

21:02.417 --> 21:04.000
amazing potatoes,
Mrs. Monroe?

21:04.000 --> 21:06.084
Oh, absolutely.

21:06.084 --> 21:09.375
They remind me of my mother's.

21:09.375 --> 21:11.583
He talks pretty.

21:11.583 --> 21:13.125
That he does.

21:13.125 --> 21:15.000
[instrumental music]

21:16.417 --> 21:19.125
- How's the tweeting going?
- Hm, decided not to bother.

21:19.125 --> 21:20.917
Too complicated.

21:20.917 --> 21:23.166
So how is anyone
supposed to know
this event is happening?

21:23.166 --> 21:25.917
I made up these
little posters.
Took me all day.

21:25.917 --> 21:28.542
I swear, you need
an owner's manual
to figure out

21:28.542 --> 21:30.042
how to use
that inkjet printer.

21:30.042 --> 21:31.375
Which is why they give you
an owner's manual.

21:31.375 --> 21:33.750
- Mom, we agreed to this.
- Well, I changed my mind.

21:33.750 --> 21:35.750
And I don't appreciate
being ordered around

21:35.750 --> 21:37.959
by my bossy-boots daughter.

21:37.959 --> 21:40.167
You know what, if I weren't
bossy, none of this would

21:40.167 --> 21:42.041
have happened,
not that it matters anyway

21:42.041 --> 21:43.667
since nobody's gonna know
about the event.

21:43.667 --> 21:45.417
See, now, why are you
always so negative?

21:45.417 --> 21:46.542
Why are you always
so helpless?

21:46.542 --> 21:47.959
I am not helpless.

21:47.959 --> 21:49.959
I just don't care about
the details like you do

21:49.959 --> 21:52.542
which is why
I let you do things
your own way.

21:52.542 --> 21:53.792
You let me?

21:53.792 --> 21:55.583
Oh, wow, mom,
that is so generous

21:55.583 --> 21:57.625
that you, you let me
do your work for you

21:57.625 --> 21:59.083
with the freedom to do it
however I want.

21:59.083 --> 22:00.750
You know, and I thought
that carrying me around

22:00.750 --> 22:03.375
for nine months in utero
was a sacrifice.

22:03.375 --> 22:04.792
I-I am truly humbled.

22:04.792 --> 22:07.500
Sarcasm gives you crow's-feet.

22:07.500 --> 22:10.042
You know, I am sick
of cleaning up
your messes.

22:10.042 --> 22:11.167
I really am.

22:11.167 --> 22:12.166
Well, then you shouldn't have
volunteered

22:12.166 --> 22:14.167
which, by the way, is what
you did, and I have witnesses.

22:14.167 --> 22:16.333
Oh, you know, well, now, I'm
un-volunteering, so good luck.

22:16.333 --> 22:18.708
Try not to screw it up.

22:18.708 --> 22:21.708
- I don't need your luck!
- 'Fine.'

22:27.042 --> 22:30.000
Oh. It is so good
to have you home.

22:31.875 --> 22:34.167
It's good to be here.

22:34.167 --> 22:36.000
I've been doing a lot of
thinking about the importance

22:36.000 --> 22:38.375
of family
ever since Charlotte's fall.

22:38.375 --> 22:41.625
I have been rigid and very
unforgiving of you, Savannah

22:41.625 --> 22:43.708
and I am sorry.

22:44.750 --> 22:47.167
It's okay, mom.

22:47.167 --> 22:50.209
I know how bad you wanted me
to stay at Mem-Chris

22:50.209 --> 22:53.792
but as you can see,
I'm doing just fine at Lancer.

22:53.792 --> 22:57.125
Well...you are changing,
though.

22:57.125 --> 23:00.750
- Well, in a good way I hope.
- Please.

23:00.750 --> 23:03.250
I mean, that boy out there..

23:03.250 --> 23:05.208
You don't like Dan?

23:05.208 --> 23:07.875
But you seemed
to really warm up to him.

23:07.875 --> 23:10.792
That boy is charming
and as slick as an eel

23:10.792 --> 23:13.375
but he's not serious,
and certainly not about you.

23:13.375 --> 23:16.167
I think he thinks
it's a big game or something.

23:16.167 --> 23:18.458
- What makes you say that?
- A mother knows.

23:18.458 --> 23:20.209
Has he made you any promises?

23:20.209 --> 23:22.542
We've only been
going out a few weeks.
I wouldn't expect him to.

23:22.542 --> 23:25.792
Oh, but he would expect you to
show that very public display

23:25.792 --> 23:28.167
of your feelings for him
at that cafe.

23:28.167 --> 23:29.750
'I don't think that
is something you
would have done'

23:29.750 --> 23:33.208
if you were still here
and going to
Memphis Christian.

23:33.208 --> 23:36.000
This conversation
officially sucks.

23:36.000 --> 23:38.291
Don't you use that word
in this house!

23:38.291 --> 23:40.458
- 'Savannah!'
- Dan, we're leaving.

23:40.458 --> 23:43.750
Savannah! Wait!

23:43.750 --> 23:45.834
I do not wanna fight anymore.

23:45.834 --> 23:47.417
Now, we all need to make
whatever compromises

23:47.417 --> 23:51.667
and sacrifices it takes
to stand together as a family.

23:51.667 --> 23:54.041
We, mom? Or me?

23:54.041 --> 23:56.000
You keep a civil tongue
in your head.

23:56.000 --> 23:58.250
When you are in this house,
you will abide by our rules.

23:58.250 --> 24:00.583
- And that includes showing--
- You've been nasty to me--

24:00.583 --> 24:02.084
And I'm sick
of putting up with it!

24:03.333 --> 24:06.209
I forgot how fun
these family dinners could be.

24:06.209 --> 24:08.000
Layne, we talked about
how this was--

24:08.000 --> 24:11.959
Back off, Parker.
I am handling this!

24:14.500 --> 24:17.209
I am handling this.

24:17.209 --> 24:20.000
Now, your father and I
have discussed this matter

24:20.000 --> 24:21.917
and here is our bottom line.

24:21.917 --> 24:24.792
We agree
you can stay
enrolled at Lancer

24:24.792 --> 24:27.500
and you can stay on
the squad there.

24:27.500 --> 24:30.083
And Dan?

24:30.083 --> 24:32.667
He is not for you, Savannah.

24:32.667 --> 24:33.875
We want you to move home

24:33.875 --> 24:36.333
spend time with boys
who are like us.

24:36.333 --> 24:39.583
Mona Fellow's son,
Noah, he would give
his good right arm

24:39.583 --> 24:41.208
to go out on a date with you.

24:41.208 --> 24:45.125
And if dating
a one-armed zealot
isn't acceptable to me?

24:45.125 --> 24:47.834
Well, then, I guess
you have a choice to make.

24:51.792 --> 24:54.500
[instrumental music]

24:54.500 --> 24:57.084
Let's go, Dan.

25:01.500 --> 25:05.959
Savannah, if you go
through that door,
there is no coming back.

25:07.250 --> 25:11.458
That doesn't
change the fact
that I love you all.

25:13.125 --> 25:14.959
Thank you for dinner.

25:15.834 --> 25:18.375
[music continues]

25:21.041 --> 25:22.500
[sighs]

25:22.500 --> 25:24.917
You okay?

25:24.917 --> 25:26.917
I'm not sure yet.

25:26.917 --> 25:29.000
I think.

25:29.000 --> 25:31.875
Guess now, I stood up to her,
it feels good.

25:31.875 --> 25:34.042
You know, she'll probably
change her mind.

25:36.000 --> 25:40.084
- Are you okay?
- Me? Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

25:40.084 --> 25:43.000
I mean...I've had more
relaxing evenings.

25:43.000 --> 25:45.209
The potatoes
were a little undercooked.

25:47.458 --> 25:50.625
I've never had anyone
disown their family over me.

25:50.625 --> 25:52.917
- Was that weird?
- Yes.

25:52.917 --> 25:54.917
Very.

25:54.917 --> 25:57.041
Well, don't make
too much of it.

25:57.041 --> 25:59.417
It really wasn't about you.

25:59.417 --> 26:01.125
It was about me.

26:01.125 --> 26:04.000
Getting clear on who I am

26:04.000 --> 26:05.917
or who I want to be.

26:05.917 --> 26:09.542
[sighs]
I mean, we're casual, right?

26:09.542 --> 26:11.250
Right.

26:11.250 --> 26:13.291
You wanna come in?

26:13.291 --> 26:16.291
It's late.
I should probably go.

26:17.708 --> 26:20.125
Okay.

26:20.125 --> 26:22.084
Goodnight.

26:24.250 --> 26:26.000
Goodnight.

26:31.834 --> 26:33.875
Oh, crap, crap, crap.

26:33.875 --> 26:36.667
- Crap.
- Marti? What's up?

26:36.667 --> 26:37.834
[sighs]

26:37.834 --> 26:40.041
- Our Wi-Fi's down again.
- Oh.

26:40.041 --> 26:42.500
You just need to reboot
the connection to the router.

26:43.375 --> 26:45.166
- Oh.
- Here.

26:46.625 --> 26:48.041
What are you trying to do?

26:48.041 --> 26:50.458
Get the word out on
my mom's open-mic night.

26:50.458 --> 26:52.750
I thought you weren't
helping mom anymore.

26:52.750 --> 26:53.959
I did say that, yes.

26:53.959 --> 26:55.792
Thank you for pointing out
my hypocrisy.

26:55.792 --> 26:59.000
So basically, you're Lewis'
flyer and your mom's base.

26:59.000 --> 27:00.875
I'm just trying
to help her succeed.

27:00.875 --> 27:02.167
Spoken like a true base.

27:02.167 --> 27:03.000
Alright, you can
stop calling me

27:03.000 --> 27:04.375
base any time now.

27:04.375 --> 27:07.042
[chuckles]

27:07.042 --> 27:09.625
There. Just let it
log back in.

27:09.625 --> 27:13.000
- Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

27:13.000 --> 27:15.834
Listen...I know I get pissed

27:15.834 --> 27:18.417
but my mom does need me.

27:18.417 --> 27:20.166
I can't just let go.

27:20.166 --> 27:23.458
Well, if a base can't let go,
a flyer never learns to fly.

27:23.458 --> 27:26.084
And what if you let go
and your flyer falls
on her ass?

27:26.084 --> 27:28.834
Well, then you
help her back up
and let her go again.

27:28.834 --> 27:31.042
Only way she learns.

27:31.042 --> 27:33.583
[instrumental music]

27:38.625 --> 27:40.125
[sighs]

27:43.708 --> 27:46.333
Hey, uh, we need to talk.

27:46.333 --> 27:47.750
Really?

27:47.750 --> 27:50.375
'Cause   I
can think
of something more fun to do.

27:50.375 --> 27:53.083
Yeah, no, that's what we need
to talk about, alright?

27:53.083 --> 27:56.000
And I need to make sure
we're on the same page here.

27:56.000 --> 27:57.000
Now, what happened
between us yesterday

27:57.000 --> 27:59.000
was just a one-time thing.

27:59.000 --> 28:00.500
Oh, until next time.

28:00.500 --> 28:01.917
'That's how it works
with us, Lewis--'

28:01.917 --> 28:03.875
No, not anymore, okay?

28:03.875 --> 28:05.708
Now, I'm done with us.

28:05.708 --> 28:07.667
And I'm done helping you
train for the bid video, too.

28:07.667 --> 28:09.417
You and Darwin
will just have to..

28:09.417 --> 28:11.500
...figure that out, alright?

28:11.500 --> 28:15.042
- I'm moving on, Alice.
- You're moving on to Marti?

28:15.042 --> 28:17.083
Yeah, see, no,
that has nothing to do
with you and me.

28:17.083 --> 28:19.166
It has everything to do
with you and me.

28:19.166 --> 28:21.583
- Okay, oh, whatever..
- Don't walk away from me!

28:21.583 --> 28:23.834
Will you stop it?

28:23.834 --> 28:25.209
'God!'

28:25.209 --> 28:27.042
I love you, Lewis.

28:28.167 --> 28:29.834
That's why I started
taking all that crap

28:29.834 --> 28:32.167
that Jake gave me..

28:32.167 --> 28:35.167
...so you wouldn't replace
me as your flyer

28:35.167 --> 28:36.500
so we could be together again.

28:36.500 --> 28:39.042
Now you said you hadn't
started taking anything yet.

28:39.042 --> 28:41.166
God, of course, I had.

28:41.166 --> 28:44.166
Duh, you're so gullible.
I still am.

28:44.166 --> 28:46.750
Okay, but I'll stop,
I promise, if you
just keep helping me--

28:46.750 --> 28:48.458
I can't do this anymore.

28:48.458 --> 28:51.167
I said don't walk away!

28:52.167 --> 28:53.959
Are you crazy?

28:55.250 --> 28:57.041
My office.

28:57.041 --> 28:58.750
Now.

28:58.750 --> 29:01.291
[music continues]

29:04.875 --> 29:06.208
[indistinct chattering]

29:08.042 --> 29:10.583
[instrumental music]

29:17.042 --> 29:18.583
Now, you.

29:20.375 --> 29:23.000
Whatever Lewis said,
it's not true.

29:23.000 --> 29:24.625
Well, he was
remarkably tight-lipped

29:24.625 --> 29:27.333
considering you just chucked
a bottle at his head.

29:27.333 --> 29:30.000
'And I noticed that you threw
with your bad hand.'

29:30.000 --> 29:33.708
You must not be feeling
any pain, huh?

29:33.708 --> 29:36.583
Lewis didn't give you up,
but he's a lousy liar.

29:36.583 --> 29:38.083
I've been down
this road before.

29:38.083 --> 29:41.084
I know how desperate
sidelined athletes can get.

29:43.542 --> 29:46.959
I'm not touching that.
That's disgusting.

29:48.417 --> 29:50.375
You're so talented, Alice.

29:51.417 --> 29:54.834
But you're putting
the entire team at risk.

29:54.834 --> 29:57.375
You're doing this because
you're afraid of losing Lewis.

29:58.083 --> 29:59.750
Am I right?

29:59.750 --> 30:01.792
[instrumental music]

30:03.333 --> 30:06.750
Everything would be fine
if I was just back
flying with him.

30:09.166 --> 30:11.209
When I was your age

30:11.209 --> 30:13.166
I obsessed over a guy

30:13.166 --> 30:16.625
and he was older
and strong and powerful..

30:17.500 --> 30:19.333
...married.

30:19.333 --> 30:22.000
And I told myself
that it was okay to chase him

30:22.000 --> 30:25.000
but it wasn't.

30:25.000 --> 30:27.166
'A lot of people got hurt.'

30:27.166 --> 30:29.291
I lied to myself

30:29.291 --> 30:32.125
just like
you're doing right now.

30:32.125 --> 30:34.625
And trust me..

30:34.625 --> 30:36.250
...move on.

30:37.333 --> 30:39.125
'I don't want know
what you're taking'

30:39.125 --> 30:41.291
but it stops   now

30:41.291 --> 30:43.834
and I want you to take it easy
for two weeks.

30:43.834 --> 30:45.167
What about the bid video?

30:45.167 --> 30:48.125
You can dance, but no flying.

30:48.125 --> 30:51.917
- And if I don't agree?
- Then you can
take a drug test.

30:51.917 --> 30:53.583
There's ways
to fool drug tests.

30:55.042 --> 30:57.750
But you can't fool me.

30:57.750 --> 31:00.041
'There is not a lie
that you can think of'

31:00.041 --> 31:02.125
that I haven't already told.

31:02.125 --> 31:04.583
[music continues]

31:13.834 --> 31:16.667
[instrumental music]

31:18.500 --> 31:20.667
Oh, this new phone
is so awesome.

31:20.667 --> 31:22.542
It has a front-facing camera,
so I can be checking out

31:22.542 --> 31:25.208
how I look and
people just think
I'm using my phone.

31:29.667 --> 31:32.000
[sighs]
You've been
really distant lately.

31:32.000 --> 31:33.834
'What's up, moody man?'

31:35.166 --> 31:37.084
'Where are you going?'

31:37.084 --> 31:38.083
Do you wanna hit up Empire?

31:38.083 --> 31:42.333
Sorry, Rosalie.
I need a rain check.

31:50.041 --> 31:51.375
[sighs]

31:52.167 --> 31:54.708
[instrumental music]

31:57.959 --> 32:01.125
- I've been calling you.
- Yeah, I turned my cell off.

32:01.125 --> 32:05.042
Just...had some
thinking to do.

32:05.042 --> 32:06.834
Come here.

32:09.250 --> 32:12.041
[music continues]

32:13.583 --> 32:15.000
I was freaking out.

32:15.000 --> 32:16.875
I, I kept thinking
you were mad

32:16.875 --> 32:19.542
and then I kept thinking you
were with some other girl.

32:19.542 --> 32:21.500
Then I considered asking Marti
the names of the other girls

32:21.500 --> 32:24.042
you dated, so I could
hunt them down
and kill them.

32:24.042 --> 32:28.000
And then it occurred to me,
I was thinking crazy
and insecure.

32:28.000 --> 32:30.417
And it was my own fault.

32:30.417 --> 32:33.500
- Dan, I lied to you.
- About what?

32:34.792 --> 32:37.375
About me being okay
with being non-exclusive.

32:38.875 --> 32:42.000
- I see.
- 'I like you so much, Dan.'

32:42.000 --> 32:46.583
But if I won't change
who I am to make
my mom happy..

32:46.583 --> 32:48.834
...I won't do it
for you, either.

32:50.500 --> 32:52.542
I'm sorry,
but it's all or nothing.

33:00.834 --> 33:03.041
Sold.

33:03.041 --> 33:04.542
What?

33:04.542 --> 33:06.625
We'll be exclusive.

33:07.750 --> 33:09.417
You better not be joking.

33:09.417 --> 33:12.000
I mean, I'm not
even your type.

33:12.000 --> 33:13.291
And I'm not yours.

33:13.291 --> 33:17.250
So, hey, we got that
in common, right?

33:17.250 --> 33:18.500
That makes no sense.

33:18.500 --> 33:19.583
Look, I've been thinking about

33:19.583 --> 33:21.792
this all day, okay?

33:21.792 --> 33:24.542
You gave up a lot
walking out on your parents.

33:24.542 --> 33:26.959
I mean, I've never been a part
of something like that.

33:26.959 --> 33:29.667
I'm sorry you got caught
in the middle of it.

33:29.667 --> 33:31.458
I was afraid
I might have scared you off.

33:31.458 --> 33:32.750
Look, Savannah,
I can't promise

33:32.750 --> 33:34.750
I'm gonna be successful
with monogamy

33:34.750 --> 33:39.167
because...I've never seen it
as a viable lifestyle choice..

33:40.667 --> 33:42.166
...but I've been blessed
with beginner's luck

33:42.166 --> 33:43.417
on more than one occasion

33:43.417 --> 33:47.209
so...I remain
cautiously optimistic.

33:49.209 --> 33:50.625
I do like optimism.

33:51.542 --> 33:52.667
Me, too.

33:52.667 --> 33:55.458
[instrumental music]

33:59.959 --> 34:01.209
[Hey Monday singing
"I Don't Wanna Dance"]

34:01.209 --> 34:02.250
♪ I don't have time ♪

34:02.250 --> 34:05.042
♪ For another game.. ♪

34:08.000 --> 34:09.500
Loving it!

34:12.667 --> 34:14.708
♪ I don't wanna dance ♪

34:14.708 --> 34:17.875
♪ You blew your chance
to rock my night ♪

34:17.875 --> 34:20.042
- Hey, baby!
- Mom, this is amazing.

34:20.042 --> 34:22.125
What'd you do to get
all these people here
on Wednesday night?

34:22.125 --> 34:25.166
Well, there was
a big fraternity party
raging at the KT house.

34:25.166 --> 34:27.083
They even got Hey Monday
and everything.

34:27.083 --> 34:30.208
So I hung my little posters
across the street

34:30.208 --> 34:31.500
saying first drink for free

34:31.500 --> 34:34.625
and then I called the cops
to bust up the party.

34:34.625 --> 34:38.208
[chuckles]
And then the Greeks
saw my little posters

34:38.208 --> 34:40.125
so they had no choice,
but to come here.

34:40.125 --> 34:43.125
- That is genius.
- Hey, this is great!

34:43.125 --> 34:44.458
Congratulations..

34:44.458 --> 34:46.167
..manager.

34:46.167 --> 34:48.833
- Whoa!
- Ah! Mom!

34:48.833 --> 34:51.500
- Well?
- Okay, fine.

34:51.500 --> 34:54.125
I-I will admit it.
You, you didn't need me.

34:54.125 --> 34:57.834
Oh! The sweetest four words
in the English language

34:57.834 --> 35:00.167
but you did the stage,
the sound system,
the planning.

35:00.167 --> 35:02.792
I could not have done this
without you.

35:02.792 --> 35:05.834
- Thanks, baby.
- You're welcome.

35:05.834 --> 35:07.583
Hey, you know what,
while we're being honest

35:07.583 --> 35:09.333
helping you makes me
feel really good.

35:09.333 --> 35:11.084
- It does?
- Yeah.

35:11.084 --> 35:13.834
There's this, this
trust dynamic between
bases and flyers--

35:13.834 --> 35:16.834
Whoa, don't-don't,
don't get psychological on me.

35:16.834 --> 35:18.084
I am half in the bag.

35:18.084 --> 35:19.208
Now, let me buy you a scotch

35:19.208 --> 35:22.042
because you don't go on
until the end.

35:22.042 --> 35:24.333
- Sounds good.
- I like the way we do things.

35:24.333 --> 35:29.333
♪ You blew your chance
to rock my night away ♪

35:29.333 --> 35:32.000
♪ I want some fun ♪

35:32.000 --> 35:35.417
♪ Boy you're
so not the one.. ♪

35:35.417 --> 35:38.167
I didn't bring any pills.

35:38.167 --> 35:39.625
Keep going through them
this fast, you're gonna get

35:39.625 --> 35:40.708
yourself into trouble.

35:40.708 --> 35:42.167
No kidding.

35:42.167 --> 35:45.583
Today I got so wound up,
I smashed a window.

35:45.583 --> 35:48.458
I don't think
the drug thing is for me.

35:48.458 --> 35:50.792
I flushed what was left.

35:50.792 --> 35:52.750
You flushed it?

35:55.333 --> 35:58.333
Do you have any idea how hard
it is to get that stuff?

36:01.458 --> 36:03.209
Maybe I can make it up to you.

36:04.708 --> 36:06.083
I'm looking for a rebound guy.

36:06.083 --> 36:09.042
- What about Lewis?
- Flushed him, too.

36:09.042 --> 36:10.792
[chuckles]

36:11.750 --> 36:13.417
Do you wanna get out of here?

36:13.417 --> 36:15.375
Sounds like a plan.

36:15.375 --> 36:18.375
♪ Oh take me home ♪

36:18.375 --> 36:21.375
[music continues]

36:21.375 --> 36:24.667
[all cheering]

36:39.458 --> 36:41.959
- Hey, you.
- Hey.

36:41.959 --> 36:44.291
Hey, um, I-I promised my mom
I'd play one song

36:44.291 --> 36:45.542
and I'm good to go.

36:45.542 --> 36:47.125
We're still on for Hi-Tone,
right?

36:47.125 --> 36:51.125
Uh, actually,
I'm a little tired.

36:51.125 --> 36:54.250
Oh. Wanna just grab
a coffee instead?

36:54.250 --> 36:57.125
You know, probably,
it's just best if we just..

36:58.875 --> 37:01.917
Look, I'm just gonna head on
back to Cheer Town, okay?

37:01.917 --> 37:03.542
Sorry.

37:07.750 --> 37:09.458
Okay, no, look, I'm sorry

37:09.458 --> 37:12.375
I just made you
feel like crap,
and that ain't right.

37:12.375 --> 37:14.667
I'm a big girl,
if you're not into it,
you don't owe me any--

37:14.667 --> 37:17.084
No, I do, okay?

37:17.084 --> 37:19.500
You know, when I first asked
you out, I was a free agent.

37:19.500 --> 37:21.375
Uh, well, I thought I was

37:21.375 --> 37:24.625
and then stuff with Alice
got complicated.

37:24.625 --> 37:26.708
By complicated, you mean..

37:26.708 --> 37:28.458
- Yeah.
- Oh, Lewis..

37:28.458 --> 37:31.166
I keep thinking I'm done with
her, and I keep being wrong.

37:31.166 --> 37:33.167
I don't know
if I'm lying to myself

37:33.167 --> 37:35.792
but...I can't move on
to something new

37:35.792 --> 37:39.209
before I figure out
what the hell
I'm doing here, Marti.

37:39.209 --> 37:42.041
So it's not me, it's you.

37:42.041 --> 37:44.542
Yeah. Something like that.

37:44.542 --> 37:46.583
[sighs]

37:46.583 --> 37:48.792
You didn't have to tell me
the truth, you know?

37:48.792 --> 37:50.333
I mean, we could
have just gone through
with it, and I never

37:50.333 --> 37:52.125
would've known
what went down
with you and Alice.

37:52.125 --> 37:55.084
Yeah, but that didn't feel
right, either, somehow.

37:57.000 --> 37:59.041
It's good to know
I can trust you.

38:00.542 --> 38:01.792
[mic squealing]

38:01.792 --> 38:03.291
(Wanda)
'Hello, everyone!'

38:03.291 --> 38:05.667
You know, I just want
to thank you all again

38:05.667 --> 38:07.209
for coming out tonight

38:07.209 --> 38:10.542
and I have saved
the best for last.

38:10.542 --> 38:14.875
I want you to
welcome my beautiful
and talented daughter

38:14.875 --> 38:16.542
Marti Perkins!

38:16.542 --> 38:19.083
[all cheering]

38:21.375 --> 38:24.417
[guitar music]

38:28.291 --> 38:30.000
♪ How many of you
people out there ♪

38:30.000 --> 38:32.333
♪ Been hurt in some kind
of love affair? ♪

38:32.333 --> 38:34.084
♪ And how many times
do you swear ♪

38:34.084 --> 38:37.042
♪ That you'll never
love again? ♪

38:37.042 --> 38:39.041
♪ How many lonely
sleepless nights? ♪

38:39.041 --> 38:41.125
♪ How many lies?
How many fights? ♪

38:41.125 --> 38:43.041
♪ And why would you
want to put yourself ♪

38:43.041 --> 38:45.125
♪ Through all of that again? ♪

